<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-estrategiasSumar" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li>427. Sample responses: I used base-ten blocks to make both numbers, then counted up the total.</li>
      <li>353. Sample response: I knew that 52 plus 1 is 53. I put that with the hundreds from the first number and got 353. </li>
      <li>394. Sample reasoning: <m>200 + 100 = 300</m><m>70 + 10 = 80</m><m>6 + 8 = 14</m><m>300 + 80 + 14 = 394</m></li>
      <li>603. Sample response: I added the hundreds to get 500. Then I added the tens to get 90 because 305 has a zero in the tens place. Then, I added the ones to get 13. This made a new ten, which then made a new hundred. After the new hundred, there were 3 ones and 6 hundreds, which makes 603.</li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


